# pyenv
#   For a library or binary, you wish to ignore your .python-version.
#   For a project, you may wish to publish it:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1191, it is recommended to not ignore Pipfile.lock.
#   If you are part of a development team or across environments, you should
#   ignore it to avoid conflicts.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   However, in some cases, such as when building a lib, you may want to ignore it.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
# .pdm-python
# .pdm-build/

